led to the blending of <ENAMEX TYPE="SUBSTANCE">fuels</ENAMEX> to lower emissions. To ensure that the
<ENAMEX TYPE="PERSON">cap</ENAMEX> is met and to provide credibility, <ENAMEX TYPE="PER_DESC">sources</ENAMEX> also are required to
install systems that continuously monitor and report emissions.
The <ENAMEX TYPE="PERSON">Acid Rain</ENAMEX> Program has proven to be an excellent model for
<ENAMEX TYPE="PERSON">cap</ENAMEX> and trade programs. Compliance with the program has been nearly
<NUMEX TYPE="PERCENT">100 percent</NUMEX> and <TIMEX TYPE="DATE">annual</TIMEX> emissions of <NUMEX TYPE="QUANTITY">SO2</NUMEX> from power <ENAMEX TYPE="FAC_DESC">plants</ENAMEX> have
already been reduced <NUMEX TYPE="QUANTITY">over 6 million tons</NUMEX> (<NUMEX TYPE="PERCENT">about 35 percent</NUMEX>) from
<TIMEX TYPE="DATE">1980</TIMEX> levels. Greater reductions earlier than expected have lowered
